  "prompt": "When is the pre placement talk of WIPRO?",
  "response": "Unfortunately, I cannot provide you with the exact date and time of Wipro's pre-placement talk.\n\n*   **These talks are specific to colleges/institutions.** Wipro (and other companies) schedules these talks directly with the training and placement offices of individual colleges.\n\n*   **Information is usually disseminated internally.** The date and time will be announced to the students of that particular college through their placement cell, department notices, or student representatives.\n\nHowever, here's what you can do to find out:\n\n1.  **Contact Your College's Placement Cell:** This is the *most important* step. They will have the official information.\n\n2.  **Check College Notice Boards (Physical and Online):** Placement announcements are usually prominently displayed.\n\n3.  **Talk to Your Department Seniors/Placement Representatives:** They may have information or know when the announcement is expected.\n\n4.  **Check Your College's Website/Social Media Groups:** Some colleges post placement-related information online.\n\n5.  **If you are part of any student groups for your department or for placements, check there.**\n\nGood luck with your placement process!\n",
